---
source: crates/splitter-cli/tests/help_snapshots.rs
expression: output
---
Display real-time statistics for all active streams managed by the
running daemon. Refreshes once per second. Press Ctrl-C to exit.

Columns: session, stream, packets sent/recv/lost, bitrate kbps, RTT ms, bandwidth.

Requires a running daemon (`splitter-cli daemon`).

Examples:
splitter-cli stats
splitter-cli stats --stream-id 1

Usage: splitter-cli stats [OPTIONS]

Options:
      --stream-id <STREAM_ID>
          

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
